<DocsLayout title="Installation">
  <h1>Installation</h1>
  <p>
    EncodeSwarmr can be deployed using Docker Compose, Linux packages, or standalone binaries. Docker Compose is the recommended method for most deployments.
  </p>

  <h2>Docker Compose (Recommended)</h2>
  <p>The quickest way to get EncodeSwarmr running with PostgreSQL.</p>

  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/badskater/encodeswarmr.git
cd encodeswarmr
docker compose up -d</code></pre>

  <p>
    This starts the Controller on port <code>8080</code> and PostgreSQL on port <code>5432</code>. Open <code>http://localhost:8080</code> to access the setup wizard.
  </p>

  <h3>Custom Configuration</h3>
  <p>Copy the example configuration and adjust settings before starting:</p>
  <pre><code>cp configs/controller.yaml.example configs/controller.yaml
# Edit configs/controller.yaml with your settings
docker compose up -d</code></pre>

  <h2>Linux Packages</h2>

  <h3>Debian / Ubuntu (.deb)</h3>
  <pre><code># Download the latest .deb from GitHub Releases
sudo dpkg -i encodeswarmr-controller_1.0.0_amd64.deb
sudo systemctl enable --now encodeswarmr-controller</code></pre>

  <h3>RHEL / Rocky / AlmaLinux (.rpm)</h3>
  <pre><code># Download the latest .rpm from GitHub Releases
sudo rpm -i encodeswarmr-controller-1.0.0.x86_64.rpm
sudo systemctl enable --now encodeswarmr-controller</code></pre>

  <h2>Building from Source</h2>
  <p>Requires Go 1.25+ and Node.js 22+.</p>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/badskater/encodeswarmr.git
cd encodeswarmr
make all</code></pre>

  <p>Build targets:</p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Target</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>make controller</code></td><td>Linux controller binary</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make agent</code></td><td>Windows agent binary</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make agent-linux</code></td><td>Linux agent binary</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make web</code></td><td>React/Vite frontend build</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make deb</code></td><td>Debian package</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make rpm</code></td><td>RPM package</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make installer</code></td><td>Windows GUI installer (Inno Setup)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Agent Installation</h2>

  <h3>Windows</h3>
  <p>Download and run the Windows installer from <a href="https://github.com/badskater/encodeswarmr/releases">GitHub Releases</a>, or install as a service from the command line:</p>
  <pre><code>encodeswarmr-agent.exe install ^
  --controller https://&lt;controller-ip&gt;:9443 ^
  --token &lt;enrollment-token&gt;</code></pre>

  <h3>Linux</h3>
  <pre><code>encodeswarmr-agent install \
  --controller https://&lt;controller-ip&gt;:9443 \
  --token &lt;enrollment-token&gt;</code></pre>

  <p>
    Enrollment tokens are generated from the Controller web UI under <strong>Settings &gt; Agents &gt; Enrollment Tokens</strong>. Tokens enable zero-touch agent registration.
  </p>

  <h2>Setup Wizard</h2>
  <p>
    On first launch, the Controller presents a setup wizard that walks you through:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Creating the initial admin account</li>
    <li>Configuring media storage paths (UNC/NFS shares)</li>
    <li>Generating your first agent enrollment token</li>
    <li>Optional: configuring OIDC SSO</li>
    <li>Optional: setting up webhook notifications</li>
  </ol>

